name: phi
description:
phi: 

The golden ratio, also known as the divine proportion, golden mean, or golden section, is a number often encountered when taking the ratios of distances in simple geometric figures such as the pentagon, pentagram, decagon and dodecahedron. It is denoted as phi.

source:
Wolfram - http://mathworld.wolfram.com/GoldenRatio.html
